text:
Sept22
Managed to re do the trail when there lesser rain. Nice walk and easier to reach from the overhead bridge that is link to kpe from upper serangoon road and sengkang

Older post
Muddy trail towards the forest, best to time it during non raining season. Was not able to make it to the end due to ponding along the trail

One of the most surreal places I've been to in Singapore, with little pockets of community that leave their mark in the space - including fishermen, gardeners, and cyclists. Under the expressway, you would think that the cars overhead would be a nuisance, but that's the beauty of it, only the sound of birds echo in that chasm. Will be a pity to see this go.
Young forest. Great potential for high value BTO with river view to be built here.
It's very quiet place, had a half an hour walk in the Tuesday morning, don't see any onehere but two street dogs.
A bit off the beaten track, but with nice views of Buangkok and Sengkang. Do note that the trail will be muddy, so make sure your shoes can afford to get dirty.
